    <!-- Start translatable Strings-->

    <!-- Strings Naming Convention - It was detected 6 types of Strings through a general Android App project, this types are gonna help us to give
    to translator a good context about our used Strings, allowing in this way to get a more precise translation when G11n (i18n and l10N) process is required.

            1. Titles
            2. Details
            3. Actions
            4. Plurals
            5. Variables
            6. Placeholders
    Use the proper prefix in your String key name and then add the String context, you must match the next pattern

            $type$_$context$

            E.g.
                <string name="title_myProfile">My Profile</string>
                <string name="detail_myProfile">In this section you can see your profile information</string>
                <string name="action_editProfile">Edit Profile</string>
                <string name="placeholder_name">Type here your public name</string>
    -->

